TO START THE CONVERTATION:

1)In order to manually install MkDocs you'll need Python (https://www.python.org/downloads/) installed on your system, as well as the Python package manager, pip.

2)If you're using a recent version of Python, the Python package manager, pip, is most likely installed by default. However, you may need to upgrade pip to the lasted version:

	pip install --upgrade pip

3)Install the mkdocs package using pip:

	pip install mkdocs

CONVERSION:

1)Clone wiki repo using this commad: git clone https://github.com/dbeaver/dbeaver.wiki.git

2)Create the "docs" folder in the mkdocs directory and move all the contents of your wiki repo to a mkdocs/docs

3)Build the documentation:

	mkdocs build

4)This will create a new directory, named site

5)Open any html file in this directory to view the result
